Marion 'Suge' Knight will stand trial on murder and attempted-murder charges following a hit-and-run in January . 
  The former rap music mogul struck two men with his pickup truck in January, killing one and seriously injuring the other . 
  Knight was rushed to hospital on Thursday for an unspecified medical emergency . 
  Judge Ronald Coen made the ruling after hearing testimony from Cle 'Bone' Sloan who was hit outside a Compton burger stand . 
  The judge also reduced bail from $25 million to $10 million . 
  Authorities contend Knight intentionally hit the men, killing Terry Carter, 55  . 
 